blockStates.name: Sunflower
blockStates.userText:
This page shows the visual code for generating 
the sunflower pattern based on Vogel's model:

r = c*sqrt*(n)
a = n*137.508°

where a is the angle, r is the distance from the 
center, n is the index number of the floret, and 
c is a constant scaling factor. The angle 137.508° 
is the golden angle which is approximated by 
ratios of Fibonacci numbers.
